# Python Environment & Library Best Practices

## Loading .env

Use `find_dotenv()` instead of manual path logic. It searches upward from the script's directory.

```python
# âœ… One-liner - no path manipulation
from dotenv import load_dotenv, find_dotenv; load_dotenv(find_dotenv())
```

Load env **before** creating clients that read from environment (e.g. OpenAI).

## General Principle

Before adding custom logic, check the library's API for built-in solutions.
